A holding company controlled by Icahn, 84, held more than 55 million shares of Hertz as of the end of the first quarter, a roughly 39% stake, according to data compiled by Bloomberg. Icahn described himself as “an investor and supporter of Hertz since 2014,” when his holding company began building its position. “I believe that based on a plan of reorganization that includes new capital, Hertz will again become a great company,” Icahn said. “I intend to closely follow the company’s reorganization and I look forward to assessing different opportunities to support Hertz in the future.” Read more: O.J., Accounting Fraud, Icahn: The Story of Hertz Going Bust Icahn wasn’t immediately available for comment. Hertz shares fell as much as 13% to $1.14 after the close of regular trading. Please note you must be a Maverick Insider to comment. Sign up here or sign in if you are already an Insider.